name: Incasan
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-4404
Reason: 1,3,4-thiadiazole is a rigid structure with a melting point of around 100°C. The presence of a nitro group can increase the melting point due to the dipole moment and hydrogen bonding potential, estimated at around +50°C. The methoxy group can also contribute to the melting point due to its ability to participate in hydrogen bonding, estimated at around +20°C. The carbonyl group can form hydrogen bonds and rigidify the structure, estimated at around +20°C. The Incasan base has a melting point of around -100°C.
